quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to set the font size and color of the paragraph:
[!raw!]
$("p").{0}("{1}", "16pt");
$("p").css("{2}", "blue");

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]CSS Properties[/h1]

Similar to the [b]html[/b]() method, the [b]css[/b]() method can be used to get and set CSS property values.
For example:
[b]HTML:[/b] [code format="html" ]<p>Some text</p>[/code]
[b]CSS[/b]:[code format="css" ]p {
  background-color:red;
  color: white;
}[/code]
[b]JS:[/b] [code format="js" codeId="1118"]$(function() {
  alert($("p").[b]css[/b]("background-color"));
  $("p").[b]css[/b]("background-color", "blue");
}); [/code]
[note]The code above alerts the background-color property of the paragraph and then sets it to blue.[/note]

